  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (the same as you would for pasta) and cook over a high heat for 10-15 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, add the <strong>chickpeas</strong> (no need to drain!) for a further 1 min until warmed through</p>\r\n<p>Once warmed through, drain and return everything to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-with-mint-orange-bulgur/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the skin from the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, removing all the white pith</p>\r\n<p>Cut the peeled <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into slices</p>\r\n<p>Cut each slice into rough pieces&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-with-mint-orange-bulgur/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly</p>\r\n<p>Combine the&nbsp;<strong>apple cider</strong><strong>&nbsp;vinegar&nbsp;</strong>with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-with-mint-orange-bulgur/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>halloumi</strong> in half, then each half into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> sticks</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-with-mint-orange-bulgur/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>halloumi sticks</strong> and cook on each side for 2-4 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-with-mint-orange-bulgur/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>orange segments</strong>, <strong>chopped mint</strong>, <strong>rocket</strong> and the <strong>dressing</strong> to the <strong>cooked bulgur</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good mix up &ndash; this is your <strong>orange &amp; mint bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-with-mint-orange-bulgur/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sesame seeds</strong>, <strong>sumac&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>oregano&nbsp;</strong>to a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grind to a fine powder &ndash; this is your<strong> za'atar</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-with-mint-orange-bulgur/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked halloumi</strong> over the <strong>mint &amp; orange bulgur</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle with the <strong>za'atar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
